column4: Rule
Corporate login credentials should be used instead of Gmail accounts
Multi-factor authentication should be enabled for all users in your org unit
User-managed service accounts should not have user managed keys
ServiceAccount should not have Admin privileges
The iam.serviceAccountUser and iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator roles should not be assigned to a user at the project level
Service account keys should be rotated every 90 days or less
Separation of duties should be enforced while assigning service account related roles to users
Cloud KMS cryptokeys should not be publicly accessible by anyone on the internet
Encryption keys should be rotated within a period of 90 days
Users should not have "Owner" permissions on a project that has cryptographic keys
API Keys are insecure and should not be used
API Key usage should be restricted to trusted sources
Projects should restrict the APIs that can be called by each API key
API keys should be rotated every 90 days
Cloud Audit Logging should be configured properly across all services and all users from a project
Sinks should be configured for all Log entries
A locked retention policy should be configured for Cloud Storage buckets
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for Project Ownership assignments/changes
Metric filter and alerts should exist for Audit Configuration Changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for Custom Role changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for VPC Network Firewall rule changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for VPC network route changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for VPC network changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for Cloud Storage IAM permission changes
Log metric filter and alerts should exist for SQL instance configuration changes
DNS logging should be enabled for VPC networks
Default network should not exist in a project
Legacy networks should not exist for a project
DNSSEC should be Enabled for Cloud DNS
RSASHA1 should not be used for signing
RSASHA1 should not be used for signing
Firewall rules should not allow connections from all IP addresses on TCP or SCTP port 22
Firewall rules should not allow connections from all IP addresses on TCP or UDP port 3389
VPC Flow logs should be Enabled for every subnet in VPC Network
Weak or insecure SSL Policys should not be used
Instances should not be configured to use the default service account
Instances should not be configured to use the default service account with full access to all Cloud APIs
SSH keys should not be used project-wide
Ensure oslogin is enabled for all instances
Ensure oslogin is Enabled for all projects
Interactive serial console support should be disabled
IP forwarding should not Enabled on Instances
Disks should be encrypted with customer-supplied encryption keys
Ensure Compute instances are launched with Shielded VM enabled
VMs should not be assigned public IP addresses
Confidential Computing should be enabled
Cloud Storage buckets should not be anonymously or publicly accessible
Bucket Policy Only should be Enabled
MySQL database instance should not allow anyone to connect with administrative privileges.
The skip_show_database database flag for a Cloud SQL MySQL instance should be set to on.
The local_infile database flag for a Cloud SQL MySQL instance should be set to off.
The log_checkpoints database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to on.
The log_error_verbosity database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to default or verbose.
The log_connections database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to on.
The log_disconnections database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to on.
The log_duration database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to on.
The log_lock_waits database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to on.
The log_statement database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to ddl.
The log_hostname database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Off.
The log_parser_stats database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Off.
The log_planner_stats database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Off.
The log_executor_stats database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Off.
The log_statement_stats database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Off.
The log_min_messages database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to warning.
The log_min_error_statement database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to Error or another value that is less strict.
The log_temp_files database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to 0.
The log_min_duration_statement database flag for a Cloud SQL Postgres instance should be set to -1.
The "external scripts enabled" database flag for a Cloud SQL Server instance should be set to off
The cross db ownership chaining database flag for a Cloud SQL SQL Server instance should be set to off.
The user connections database flag for a Cloud SQL for SQL Server instance should not be configured
The user options database flag for a Cloud SQL SQL Server instance should not be configured
The remote access database flag for a Cloud SQL SQL Server instance should be set to off
The 3625 (trace flag) database flag for a Cloud SQL SQL Server instance should be set to on
The contained database authentication database flag for a Cloud SQL SQL Server instance should be set to off.
Cloud SQL database instances should not be publicly accessible by anyone on the internet
Cloud SQL instances should not have public IP addresses
Automated backups for a Cloud SQL instance should be enabled.
Datasets should not be publicly accessible by anyone on the internet
BigQuery tables should have a customer-managed encryption key (CMEK) set
Datasets should have a default customer-managed encryption key (CMEK) set
